  <div class="col-md-12 text-left paddNone">\r\n                    	<h4>Deepa & Kiran Ghodgoankar</h4>\r\n                        <h5>Wedding Date: April 11, 2009</h5>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clearfix"></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="col-md-12">\r\n            	<div class="tesiBx">\r\n                <div class="col-md-9">\r\n                	<p><i class="fa fa-quote-left fa-1x"></i>\r\n                    I was referred to Amy by a friend, and am ever so grateful to have found her. I decided I needed a coordinator less than one month before my wedding, and Amy was able and willing to be flexible with my timeline, budget and various needs. From start to finish, she was great to work with. Her professionalism impressed me from the get go, as she responded to my online inquire almost immediately and had a final contract available within just days. She helped me tie a major loose end - less than one month before the wedding I didn''t have a florist I was happy with; Amy found one with a beautiful portfolio and a creative mind. In the days leading up to the wedding, it comforted me wonders to know I was working with somebody who knew weddings so well. We had a mixed Scottish-Pakistani wedding, with a mix of guests from different backgrounds and faiths. Amy was able to help us iron out the fine details from the interfaith wording of our ceremony, to the seating and everything in between. Her presence brought things together, without infringing on the uniqueness and DIY approaches we were striving for. It was a pleasure working with Amy, and I would strongly recommend her to anybody planning a wedding. There''s only so much a bride should stress about handling, the details should be left to professionals.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-3">\r\n                <img src="[php snippet=1]/images/t12.jpg" class="img-responsive img-circle" alt=""/>\r\n                